couple good points though, being the rotation of the epic quest calendar members.<br>
 rotation would need to be set so each guild in the rotation has an equal number of &quot; set chances &quot; vrs guilds calling in the same guild every time they need help. thus looking like abuse. If the same guild is continually getting called in to take these gods down, they're gonna be considered &quot; greedy &quot; or &quot; favored&quot; and things like that. only fair way to do it with the epic calendar guilds / alliances is to have a set rotation for this to happen.<br>
Just my thoughts on it.<br>
<br>
I think items like soul leech, mage staff off inny, and things like that should go to the epic calendar guilds for 1 reason. they're getting the rest of the loot, and they wouldnt have taken the god down anyhow. sound unreasonable? <br>
think of it this way, if you dont call in someone to help you're not gonna take the god down ( speaking for instance not about anyone specifically ). If you're not gonna be able to take down the god then you wouldnt have gotten it anyhow. when you can take down the god you'll be able to get those epic quest items, thus more reason to learn how to do it.<br>
Again, just my thoughts on it.<br>
If a guild accepts the epic calendar agreement and calendar reservations they've accepted the majority vote that those helping guilds would receive the quest items. i wouldnt think anyone would have a problem with that.<br>
We can hash out the ideas of &quot; well if so and so doesnt coincide then whats their punishment &quot; all year long and that'll go nowhere. Giving the epic quest items to the &quot;Big brother&quot; &quot; or big sister &quot; if ya wanna get specific =) is a very small price for what that posting guild/alliance is offering for everything they get in return. dont think that'll be a problem.<br>
As it is right now i dont see anyone being called in to do this without making a deal for something. this is just a deal for an item that might not even drop.<br>
