At 5pm PST we had 20+ Deus Factum people (gobs of planes experience, avg lvl 54-56) begging to join the raid to reach Cazic - just sitting in Feerrott wanting to run in. Because of the 2/3 rule, we didn't let anyone else join the raid until 11:30pm PST. And by that time, with folks finding other raids in HS, Sebilis, etc... 20 people was now 8 people - and some of the Europe and East Coasters were bailing...<br>
<br>
Deus has not reached Isle 5 in Air... but we can take down Cazic. We have an alliance with the smaller guild, but not for posting. SO, since we wanted to conform to the 2/3 rule, we didn't overload the raid to make sure we didn't &quot;break the rules&quot;<br>
<br>
In that situation - what's the right thing to do? Is it to call in KEG/BoTS/CIW instead of our 20 people? Or take exception to the 2/3 rule because Cazic is up. We had an enchanter who was chomping at the bit to get his FA Quest item... but we followed the rules and left Cazic to Requiem of Souls, they had Fear the next day, and they took him down.<br>
